author: {'type_string': 'Solo traveller', 'helpful_vote_count': 0, 'type': 'solo_traveller', 'countrycode': 'us', 'city': '', 'name': 'Alan', 'nr_reviews': 0, 'user_id': 251826310, 'age_group': ''}

cons:
1. The liquid hand soap and shampoo, conditioner, and body wash all had an odd and slightly unpleasant odor. I bought my own supplies for the my 2-week+ stay. Also got my own moisturizer lotion, since none was supplied. 
2. The economy room was very small, with barely enough room to walk between the bed and my suitcases, with one on a stand and another on the carpet against the wall.
3. There are only 3 laundry rooms with a single washing machine & dryer in each. (On my last night, someone brought their wet laundry and put it in the dryer ahead of me, while both dryers on the other floors were in use.)
pros:
1. Attentive, considerate, helpful, polite, and efficient staff. For example, they helped me arrange takkyuu-bin (home delivery) of 2 suitcases with the delivery company, which saved me a lot of trouble. They let me borrow a small table as a nightstand. Someone came to show me how to open the window. The maids were friendly and worked hard to clean the room thoroughly (every 3rd day, due to the pandemic). The front desk clerks reissued my room key without delay when I accidentally locked myself out of the room. 
2. Elegant, spacious lobby with comfortable chairs.
3. Bargain rates (through an internet agency; slightly higher if you book directly with the front desk, as I found out when I asked to extend my stay for an extra couple of nights).
4. Comfortable bed, fairly quiet room (some noise from closing of doors by other guests), nice wide desk. Fast & free wifi for each floor and lobby. Room is well equipped with a small fridge, luggage stand, humidifier, sophisticated air conditioner/heater/dehumidifier/fan (which you can control, if you read Japanese or follow the detailed translation guide); excellent room lights, nightlight, lamp; 27‚Äù HDTV; and slack presser (instead of an iron, for safety reasons).
5. Washer & dryer available for low cost (about Y300-400 total per load) on 3 of 14 floors. I did several loads.
6. Pleasant view of the tree-lined street and modern, tall buildings from most of the rooms.
title: Wonderful hotel for business or pleasure

stayed_room_info: {'room_id': 270786804, 'photo': {'url_square60': 'https://cf.bstatic.com/images/hotel/square60/137/137004895.jpg', 'url_original': 'https://cf.bstatic.com/images/hotel/max500/137/137004895.jpg', 'url_640x200': 'https://cf.bstatic.com/images/hotel/640x200/137/137004895.jpg', 'url_max300': 'https://cf.bstatic.com/images/hotel/max300/137/137004895.jpg', 'photo_id': 137004895, 'ratio': 1.5}, 'checkin': '2022-05-01', 'room_name': ' Double Room with Small Double Bed - Non-Smoking', 'checkout': '2022-05-04'}
pros:
well located for easy walk to shinbashi/shiodome, tsukiji and of course the ginza area. 

there‚Äôs a 7/11 on the ground floor and lots of other convenience stores in the vicinity. 

a good-size don quixote is less than 5 mins away for last minute souvenirs or other necessities. 

the room is compact but well laid out. the bath was nice and roomy. 
the sink being in the room area itself was interesting. i didn‚Äôt mind it. the built-in dehumidifier works extra hard to keep the room dry and there‚Äôs also a small humidifier in the room if needed.

restocking the water each day was great. most hotels i‚Äôve been to don‚Äôt do so. 

pajamas were super comfy. i would buy them. 

many sockets and cables to keep devices charged. 

for travelers at the end of their trip, the room had information on sending luggage to the airport. 

staff was friendly and other guests during my stay were very courteous.
title: comfy stay

cons: Could do with more amenities like a gym and a swimming pool. The bathroom could be a touch larger. The restaurant has a good Japanese food, but their 'western' breakfast set-menu is a strange mixture, including a piece of fatty, cold bacon and a thin sausage and lettuce with a small croissant, full yoghurt, and very small bits of melon and kiwi, a cup of oily soup. I would prefer a simpler, less fatty food with plain fruits, and healthier bread. (Having said that they are trying, I can tell.)
pros: Location is the greatest, just in the departure floor of the international terminal. Room is comfortable, TV, tea facility, clean and plenty of water, clean modern toilet (with bottom-washing facility, of course!) The restaurant is open till late and we can get food if we arrive in the evening. Hygiene - anti-Covid notice and hand-cleaner everywhere, so feels safe.
title: Great location, convenient, comfortable enough though without holiday-like relaxation.

cons: The breakfast was not worth ¬•1650.  I would definitely not recommend eating breakfast there unless you are okay with salad, yogurt, hard boiled eggs, bread, juice and coffee.  I was shocked that they do not offer scrambled eggs, bacon, waffles or pancakes for that price.
pros:
I chose a room with a queen bed.  The room also has a couch which is uncommon in most Japanese hotels.  I
like how the toilet is in a separate room from the bathroom.  Additionally, the shower has powerful water pressure.  The location of the hotel is very convenient.  It‚Äôs only a five minute walk to the Ginza Line which will take you straight to Shibuya in 15 minutes without having to change trains or platforms .  I reduced the number of nights because I thought I had an early flight the next day but I was wrong.  As a result, I had to add an additional night which was at a considerably higher rate but a staff member (Mr. Daya) was gracious enough to charge me the lower rate.  I absolutely recommend this hotel.  I look forward to my my next stay.
title: Great room, perfect location.

author: {'type_string': 'Solo traveller', 'user_id': 575776262, 'city': '', 'nr_reviews': 0, 'avatar': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gio9iqcXDsuDKv6qEEVBq2oZh8oUpYBsAnXPkGTIw=s96-c64', 'age_group': '', 'type': 'solo_traveller', 'helpful_vote_count': 0, 'name': 'Nayola', 'countrycode': 'jp'}

cons:
- The scale in the bathroom didn't work... or if it did, it was very hard for me (and other guests) to figure out how to use.
- My room faced Mori Tower which lit up beautifully at night, but it also faced a HUGE cemetery as well, lol. And since I saw it at night, it was even creepier... If you can, try to get the room NOT facing the cemetery...
- I had to do some work for a few hours so it would have been nice to have a desk and proper chair, but I know that would totally ruin the stylish layout of the room so it can't be helped...
pros:
- The Sky Spa on the 15th floor was amazing, both in the morning and at night. Not many places you can stay which have a spa on the 15th floor for such a good price!
- They had a sauna in the bath too!
- The layout and lighting of the room made it look so stylish and chic! I felt like I was in a five star hotel!
- The bed was sooooo comfortable I slept sooo well!
- Price was very reasonable for the location, amenities, bath, facilities, etc.
title: 4.5-star experience for a reasonable price!

author: {'user_id': 13533684, 'type_string': 'Group of friends', 'city': '', 'age_group': '', 'nr_reviews': 0, 'countrycode': 'au', 'name': 'Sara', 'helpful_vote_count': 0, 'type': 'review_category_group_of_friends'}

cons: Rooms are very small (I know it is not uncommon in Japan) but this does have very limited room for luggages. No closet (so you can't even hide the mess) and we ended up lining the suitcases against the wall leaving a very narrow alley to walk inside the room.  There are only two jointly operated washing machine/dryers in the building - definitely not enough machines. The situation gets worse in winter as it takes a lot longer to dry clothes (extra time and money).
pros: Very good location - closest metro station/ family store are only 2 mins walk. Hotel staff were super friendly and helpful - they speak fluent English. They helped us booked taxis and communicated well with the taxi drivers on our behalf.  Our family and friends enjoyed the onsen very much. In-room supplies meet expectations (standard toiletries like any reasonable hotel, coffee/ tea/ water) - no obvious missing items but nothing surprising either. They were able to accomodate my requests (high floor and away from lift). Good view from our room as it was facing the Tokyo Tower (though a couple of our friends faced the other side of the building where they had cemetery view).
title: Convenience location, great client services team but very tiny rooms

author: {'name': 'Evgeniy', 'type_string': 'Solo traveller', 'countrycode': 'ru', 'user_id': 96753356, 'nr_reviews': 0, 'age_group': '', 'avatar': 'https://graph.facebook.com/v2.9/10207026022265703/picture?type=square&height=64&width=64', 'helpful_vote_count': 4, 'city': '', 'type': 'solo_traveller'}

cons: The low for me was walking down to breakfast and seeing the chef brace himself against a big bowl of food, sneeze violently into it three times, and then cover the sneezed-on part with a bit more food and put it on the table for the breakfast buffet. Then he went back to the kitchen and was wiping his nose with his bare hands, which he hadn't washed, and sneezing more on the food. The breakfast is very expensive for the area, but I was heading to a big work meeting and couldn't afford to get sick. I hated to leave it and hated more to be rude‚Äînever in my life have I sent food back or complained to a manager about a service worker. But I did leave instead of eating, and only mentioned it at check-out because I didn't eat the breakfast (they still charged me). The person brought over a man on duty, and he became extremely cold and kind of confrontational. I don't really mind paying for the breakfast but was kind of shocked by how aggressively the manager responded. I'm writing this review in early March, but this happened about three weeks ago so I wasn't worried about Coronavirus or anything like that. I think the man just had a cold and his nose was running and he was trying to cook while also sneezing and it was just getting into the food.

stayed_room_info: {'checkout': '2020-03-14', 'room_name': 'Corner King Room Tokyo Tower Side - Non-Smoking', 'checkin': '2020-02-29', 'photo': {'photo_id': 251024152, 'url_original': 'https://cf.bstatic.com/images/hotel/max500/251/251024152.jpg', 'url_square60': 'https://cf.bstatic.com/images/hotel/square60/251/251024152.jpg', 'ratio': 1.5003663003663, 'url_max300': 'https://cf.bstatic.com/images/hotel/max300/251/251024152.jpg', 'url_640x200': 'https://cf.bstatic.com/images/hotel/640x200/251/251024152.jpg'}, 'room_id': 17980110}
pros: It was my second time staying in this hotel, and it was just as excellent as last time. I especially liked the extraordinary view. This of course depends on the room. The hotel lobby is at the 25th floor, and the guest rooms are located above that. If you book a room "with Tokyo Tower View" its pretty much guaranteed that your view on Tokyo is not obstructed by other skyscrapers and also that you're also looking towards the direction of Mount Fuji that can be seen if the weather conditions allow it. I also liked the beautiful atrium of the hotel (where the breakfast buffet is located) and of course the excellent transport connections of the location Shiodome: There is direct access to Yurikamome- and the ≈åedo-Line, and you can use an underground connection to Shimbashi-station that gives access to Yamanote-Line and many others. Ginza and the exceptionally beautiful Hamarikyu gardens is well within walking distance. Shimbashi is a very interesting area to explore with tons of small and very japanese (non-touristy) little spots for eating and drinking. Directly in the basement of Shiodome Media Tower, where the hotel is located, there are several small and good value restaurants, and even a small supermarket that is open all the time, and can be reached with the Elevator, which is extremely convenient.
title: Good value hotel

pros: Getting to be my first choice place to stay in Tokyo now, 5th time to stay here in 5 months. Location is good for access to Tokyo, both by rail and road. Room is adequate for one person, but great value. Bathroom well-equipped. Car parking available, plenty of room around the car for unloading/ loading. Due to Covid, they are now providing take-out meals to guests, cooked in the restaurant, simple menus, but well cooked and presented, and at a reasonable price. Internet access is great, wired 94/89 Mbps down/ up, wireless 62/49 down/ up, with easy log-on. Good sized work desk, with power sockets nearby, sofa to relax on or store bags.
title: My first choice hotel to stay in Tokyo!

cons: Although I understand the rationale, I was disappointed to be unable to store my luggage overnight following checkout.

pros: Second time to stay there, again during a business trip to Tokyo. Good location, ample discounted parking, excellent facilities, though limited due to current Covid pandemic. Staff helpful, making the most of the situation, and helping the guests. Good, speedy WiFi, easy to access. Convenience store nearby, so did not starve! Room is very spacey for this price level in Tokyo, ample sized work desk, table and small sofa; the bathroom is good too.
title: Great value, good location, helpful staff.
